0risk%20of%20mood%20disorders%20like%20depression%20and%20anxiety%2C%20according%20to%20a%202019%20study%20in%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov%2F30594025%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EJournal%20of%20Psychiatric%20Research%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E.%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20considering%20your%20work%20area%2C%20direct%20sunlight%20may%20actually%20exacerbate%20anxiety%2C%20but%20indirect%20sunlight%20can%20help%20people%20be%20more%20committed%20to%20and%20satisfied%20with%20their%20job%2C%20reported%20a%202016%20study%20in%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov%2F27214041%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EPLoS%20One%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThough%20some%20people's%20living%20rooms%20may%20already%20flood%20with%20sunlight%2C%20others%20have%20to%20get%20creative.%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fwww.thinkchicinteriors.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EInterior%20designer%20Malka%20Helft%3C%2Fa%3E%20recommended%20to%20Insider%20using%20natural%20light%20lamps%20that%20double%20as%20a%20decorative%20item%20to%20create%20faux%20sunshine.%20And%20if%20you%20have%20the%20luxury%20of%20a%20well-lit%20space%2C%20re-situate%20your%20desk%20or%20your%20favorite%20chair%20to%20be%20near%20the%20window%20where%20you%20can%20be%20cozy%20and%20calm.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cem%3ETry%20these%20to%20let%20the%20sunshine%20in%3A%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EStock%20up%20on%20plants%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223541%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22women%20plant%20living%20room%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5febac04b7ab82001943e82b%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222656%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EOscar%20Wong%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EPeople%20who%20had%20to%20spend%20a%20lot%20of%20time%20at%20home%20during%20the%20novel%20coronavirus%20pandemic%C2%A0had%20better%20mental%20health%20if%20they%20were%20exposed%20to%20greenery%20regularly%2C%20including%20indoor%20house%20plants%2C%20an%20outdoor%20garden%2C%20or%20even%20living%20in%20a%20greener%20neighborhood%2C%20according%20to%20a%20recent%20study%20published%20in%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov%2F33157110%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EEnvironmental%20Research%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%20It%20helped%20them%20feel%20like%20they%20were%20away%20from%20home%2C%20even%20when%20indoors%2C%20the%20researchers%20explained.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20something%20interior%20designers%20like%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.allthingstaj.com%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ETaj%20Hunter%20Waite%3C%2Fa%3E%20have%20long%20known.%20Waite%20told%20Insider%20that%20incorporating%20biophilia%20(or%20a%20love%20of%20nature)%20into%20your%20home%20can%20put%20you%20in%20a%20more%20relaxed%2C%20open%2C%20and%20positive%20mindset.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%202019%20Australian%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov%2F30539231%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estudy%20found%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20when%20people%20were%20hospitalized%20and%20stuck%20in%20a%20single%20room%20for%20the%20better%20part%20of%20three%20months%2C%20those%20who%20had%20flowering%20plants%20to%20look%20at%20were%20less%20depressed%20than%20those%20who%20had%20no%20plants.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELeverage%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhouseplants-ease-stress-guide-to-how-to-look-after-them-2020-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecalming%20power%20of%20mother%20nature%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20incorporating%20more%20plants%20into%20your%20rooms%2C%20creating%20clear%20sightlines%20to%20the%20great%20outdoors%2C%20and%20changing%20up%20how%20you%20style%20your%20windows.%20As%20an%20example%2C%20a%20simple%20sheer%2C%20flowy%20curtain%20could%20feel%20calmer%20than%20a%20bulky%20dark-colored%20one.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIf%20you%20want%20to%20adopt%20more%20plants%20but%20have%20a%20hard%20time%20keeping%20them%20alive%20or%20don't%20have%20a%20ton%20of%20natural%20light%2C%20heed%20the%20advice%20of%20urban%20farmer%20and%20plant%20expert%2C%20Nick%20Cutsumpas%3A%20He%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fhome%2Fbest-houseplants%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epreviously%20told%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%20varieties%20like%20pothos%20and%20spider%20plants%20are%20hearty%20and%20easy-to-care-for%2C%20while%20others%20like%20monstera%20deliciosa%20and%20snake%20plants%20don't%20need%20much%20light%20and%20are%20visually%20striking%20when%20you%20walk%20in%20a%20room.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnother%20tip%3A%20Plants%2C%20particularly%20trendy%2C%20Instagram-able%20varieties%2C%20can%20be%20expensive%2C%20so%20ask%20your%20green%20thumb-friends%20if%20they%20can%20cut%20you%20a%20propagation%20of%20their%20healthy%20children%2C%20and%20then%20you%20can%20grow%20your%20own%20for%20free.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIf%20you%20aren't%20blessed%20with%20a%20green%20thumb%2C%20opt%20for%20fake%20plants%20or%20flora%20and%20fauna%20art%20%E2%80%94%20even%20viewing%20pictures%20of%20nature%20helps%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov%2Fpmc%2Farticles%2FPMC4690962%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elower%20stress%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov%2Fpmc%2Farticles%2FPMC4929355%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eimprove%20attention%3C%2Fa%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cem%3ETry%20these%20to%20add%20biophilia%20design%3A%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fstr